        [
            // Page 1 - Overview and Basic Features
            `
                <h4>Customer Management - Overview</h4>
                <p>This page allows you to manage customer information and maintain customer records in a hierarchical tree structure.</p>

                <h5>Main Features:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Create New Customer:</strong> Click the "+ New" button to add a new customer or customer group</li>
                    <li><strong>Tree Structure:</strong> Customers are organized in a hierarchical tree on the left panel</li>
                    <li><strong>Search Customers:</strong> Use the search box to quickly find customers by name or ID</li>
                    <li><strong>View Customer List:</strong> View all customers in a sortable data grid with filtering options</li>
                    <li><strong>Edit Customers:</strong> Select any customer to view and edit their complete information</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete Customers:</strong> Remove inactive or duplicate customer records</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Tree Navigation:</h5>
                <p>The left panel displays customers organized by groups (e.g., "Customers (Lazimpat)"). Click on any customer to view or edit their details in the main panel.</p>

                <h5>Data Grid Features:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sortable columns - Click on column headers to sort</li>
                    <li>Drag and drop columns to reorder</li>
                    <li>Search and filter customers quickly</li>
                    <li>Action buttons for Edit, Delete, and View details</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 2 - Creating New Customers
            `
                <h4>Creating New Customers</h4>

                <h5>How to Create a New Customer:</h5>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the "+ New" button in the top right corner</li>
                    <li>The Customer Model form will open</li>
                    <li>Fill in the required customer information (marked with *)</li>
                    <li>Complete all tabs with relevant information</li>
                    <li>Click "Save" to add the customer to the system</li>
                </ol>

                <h5>Required Fields:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Name in English:</strong> Customer's official name (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Select customer type from dropdown (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Permanent Address:</strong> Customer's permanent address (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Account Map:</strong> Link to accounting chart of accounts (Required)</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Customer Model Tabs:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>General/Office Info:</strong> Basic customer information and contact details</li>
                    <li><strong>Owner/Contact:</strong> Owner and contact person details</li>
                    <li><strong>Location/others:</strong> Address and location mapping</li>
                    <li><strong>Account/Opening Bills:</strong> Account setup and opening balances</li>
                    <li><strong>Terms & Conditions:</strong> Payment terms and conditions</li>
                    <li><strong>Distribution Status:</strong> Distribution and dealer information</li>
                    <li><strong>Price History:</strong> Historical pricing information</li>
                    <li><strong>Item Map:</strong> Map items specific to this customer</li>
                    <li><strong>Bank Map:</strong> Customer's bank account details</li>
                    <li><strong>Dealer Map:</strong> Dealer assignment and mapping</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 3 - Customer Information Fields
            `
                <h4>Customer Information Fields</h4>

                <h5>Basic Information:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Auto Gen.Code:</strong> System-generated customer code (Shortcut field)</li>
                    <li><strong>Name in English:</strong> Customer name in English (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>In Nepali:</strong> Customer name in Nepali language</li>
                    <li><strong>Parent:</strong> Parent customer group (e.g., "Customers (Lazimpat)")</li>
                    <li><strong>Customer Id:</strong> Unique customer identification number</li>
                    <li><strong>Group Id:</strong> Customer group identifier</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Customer Types and Categories:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Under Group:</strong> Primary customer classification (PRIMARY by default)</li>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Customer type selection (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Party Type:</strong> Business party type classification</li>
                    <li><strong>Prefix/Start ID:</strong> Custom prefix for customer numbering</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Contact Information:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Permanent Address:</strong> Official registered address (Required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Temporary Address:</strong> Current or alternate address</li>
                    <li><strong>Tel/Mobile:</strong> Primary contact number</li>
                    <li><strong>Tel/Mobile 2:</strong> Secondary contact number</li>
                    <li><strong>Tel/Mobile 3:</strong> Additional contact number</li>
                    <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> Customer's email for communication</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Tax and Compliance:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>PAN/VAT No:</strong> Tax registration number</li>
                    <li><strong>Excise No:</strong> Excise registration if applicable</li>
                    <li><strong>GST No:</strong> Goods and Services Tax number</li>
                    <li><strong>TIN No:</strong> Tax Identification Number</li>
                    <li><strong>IEC No:</strong> Import Export Code</li>
                </ul>
            `,

            // Page 4 - Location and Additional Details
            `
                <h4>Location and Additional Details</h4>

                <h5>Location Map:</h5>
                <p>Map the customer's location using geographical identifiers:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>City:</strong> Select city from dropdown</li>
                    <li><strong>District:</strong> Select district/province</li>
                    <li><strong>Region:</strong> Geographic region classification</li>
                    <li><strong>Zone:</strong> Zone or area designation</li>
                    <li><strong>Country:</strong> Customer's country</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Branch and Dealer Assignment:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Branch Name:</strong> Assign customer to a specific branch</li>
                    <li><strong>Dealing Person:</strong> Assign a sales representative or account manager</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Customer Status Flags:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Cash Customer Y/N:</strong> Mark if customer operates on cash basis</li>
                    <li><strong>Active Customer:</strong> Enable/disable customer account</li>
                    <li><strong>Export Party:</strong> Mark if customer is involved in export business</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Export Party Details:</h5>
                <p>For customers marked as Export Party, complete additional fields:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>GST No. - Export GST registration</li>
                    <li>TIN No. - Export tax identification</li>
                    <li>IEC No. - Import Export Code for international trade</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Account Mapping:</h5>
                <p><strong>Account Map (Required):</strong> Link the customer to an account in your Chart of Accounts. This determines where customer transactions will be posted in your accounting system.</p>
            `,

            // Page 5 - Managing and Best Practices
            `
                <h4>Managing Customers - Best Practices</h4>

                <h5>Editing Existing Customers:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Click on customer name in the tree or data grid</li>
                    <li>Update information in any of the available tabs</li>
                    <li>Click "Save" to update the customer record</li>
                    <li>Use "Cancel" to discard changes</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Using the Data Grid:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Click column headers (Customer Name, Address, TEL, EMAIL, ACCOUNT) to sort</li>
                    <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Use the search box to filter customers</li>
                    <li><strong>Grouping:</strong> Drag column headers to group by that column</li>
                    <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Use the action buttons (Edit, Delete, View) for quick operations</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Best Practices:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Complete Information:</strong> Fill in as much customer information as possible for better record keeping</li>
                    <li><strong>Unique Identifiers:</strong> Ensure customer codes and IDs are unique</li>
                    <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> Keep contact information and addresses up to date</li>
                    <li><strong>Proper Categorization:</strong> Assign correct customer types and groups</li>
                    <li><strong>Account Mapping:</strong> Always map customers to appropriate accounts</li>
                    <li><strong>Tax Information:</strong> Keep PAN/VAT numbers current for compliance</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Important Notes:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Customers with active transactions cannot be deleted</li>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Mark inactive customers using the "Active Customer" checkbox instead of deleting</li>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Export party details are required for international customers</li>
                    <li><strong>Note:</strong> Account mapping affects how transactions are posted in accounting</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Search Tips:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Search by customer name, ID, or location</li>
                    <li>Use the tree structure for browsing by groups</li>
                    <li>Use data grid filters for advanced searches</li>
                    <li>Bookmark frequently accessed customers</li>
                </ul>
            `
        ]
    );
</script>
